ruler, fr. <?/ to lead, rule: cf. F. <ets>hi⟦eacute⟧rarque</ets>.]</ety>
<def>One who has high and controlling authority in sacred things; the
chief of a sacred order; <as>as, princely <ex>hierarchs</ex></as>.</def>
